Class Filters

java.lang.Object
  com.genzis.filtro.Filters

public class Filters
extends Object

Class which provides static methods to filter any map, list or set instance you already have.

filterMapKeys

public static <K,V> Map<K,V> filterMapKeys(Map<K,V> map,
                                           List<Filter<K>> filters,
                                           boolean filter_original)
                              throws InstantiationException,
                                     IllegalAccessException
Method to filter map using keys based on the filters provided.

Parameters:
map - The map to be filtered
filters - The list of filters.
filter_original - Flag indicating whether the filter change should be done to the original map passed or a new instance of map should be returned. A true value will remove entries from map which fails a filter. A false value will keep original map intact and will return a new map instance after filter.
Returns:
A map instance with values after filter.
Throws:
InstantiationException
IllegalAccessException
